    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The Test conditions factor achieves level 2 against a required level of 3, representing a known gap; however, the overall evidence from the systematic literature review across 14 published sources is judged sufficient to support a Medium assurance level for this COU. The FEA predictions are consistent with published F1717 compression-bending data for non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs, and all QoI acceptance criteria are satisfied. The credibility assessment team accepts the model for the stated COU.",
